This message implies that you need to enter in http:// URLS even on a https:// server. This can lead to mixed content warnings. We need to re-word this to make sense under the http:// and https:// case.

We could customise the message based upon the scheme tomcat sees, however, this is not necessarily the scheme that the users browser is using (e.g. Browser -> HTTPS -> Apache HTTPd -> HTTP -> Tomcat). 

Maybe some documentation with a link from the icon picker.

