When you try to install a plugin and the "Downloading and Installing" window don't finishes, there is no option to cancel this until gets a timeout. And after that, when you go back to the UPM it tries to re-download and re-install that same plugin, with no way to cancel or interrupt the process! The plugin audit log does not show this new installation happening.

Steps to reproduce:

- Change the system language to _Spanish (Spain);
- Create 2 projects (i.e. *Project X* and *Project Y*);
- Create 2 issues on *Project X* (_test 1_ and _test 2_);
- Open the issue _test 2_;
- Click on _More Actions > Convert to Sub-task_ and make it a sub-task of the issue _Test 1_;
- Open the issue _Test 1_;
- Click on _More Actions > Move_;
- In the _new project_, select the *Project Y* (you can keep the same issue type);
- In the step 4 (confirmation), it will appear a _Note_ with a variable instead the issue name.

